HEADWORD: Godchild
<hw>God"child`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One for whom a
person becomes sponsor at baptism, and whom he promises to see educated
as a Christian; a godson or goddaughter. See
<er>Godfather</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

